  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TPa18">
<l>untu mata kaḷiṟṟaṉ ōṭāta tōḷ valiyaṉ</l>
<l>nantakōpālaṉ marumakaḷē nappiṉṉāy</l>
<l>kantam kamaḻum kuḻali kaṭai tiṟavāy</l>
<l>vanteṅkum kōḻi yaḻaittaṉa kāṇ mātavip</l>
<l>pantal mēl pal kāl kuyiliṉaṅkaḷ kūviṉa kāṇ</l>
<l>pantār virali uṉ maittuṉaṉ pēr pāṭac</l>
<l>centāmaraik kaiyāl cīrār vaḷai yolippa</l>
<l>vantu tiṟavāy makiḻntēlōr empāvāy.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>O daughter-in-law of</l>
<l rend="indent">Nandagopāla, who possesses elephants oozing out must,</l>
<l rend="indent">he with strong , unconquered shoulders,</l>
<l>O Nappiṉṉai! O woman with hair that emits fragrance!</l>
<l rend="indent">Open the door.</l>
<l rend="indent">See, the fowl have emerged [from sleep] everywhere and called out!</l>
<l rend="indent">See, the flocks of koels have cried many times on the pandal of mātavi -creepers.</l>
<l>O woman with fingers that hold a ball!</l>
<l>As we sing the glories of your Husband,</l>
<l>come and open [the door] rejoicingly, with [your] red-lotus hands</l>
<l rend="indent">so that [your] bangles filled with beauty resounds!</l>
<l>O our maidens, accept [and] consider [this] attentively!</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
